-- crafter.lua
--[[                                   -
Minecraft, OpenComputers/Computercraft (or anything, really)
A library for crafting using machines, allowing for many outputs.
WIP - UNFINISHED
-                                   ]]--
-- local crafter = require("crafter")

local crafter = {}

function crafter:new(tbl)
    tbl = tbl or {}
    assert(type(tbl) == "table", "table expected")
    tbl.interfaces = {}
    tbl.recipes = {}
    tbl.gives_item = {}
    setmetatable(tbl, self)
    return tbl
end

--[[                   -
:add_interface(name: string, input: function, retrieve: function[, ftype: string])
Add functions to access a machine.
name - Name of machine
input(...) - Navigate to a machine and input specified items.
retrieve(...) - Same as input, but for retrieval.
ftype - Switch function signature.
    "part" - input(item, count, index), for all items (default)
    "whole" - input(recipe, count)
-                   ]]--
function crafter:add_interface(name, input, retrieve, ftype)
    -- TODO: find a true iscallable()
    assert(type(input) == "function", "input function required")
    assert(type(retrieve) == "function", "retrieve function required")
    ftype = tostring(ftype or "part")
    assert(({part=1, whole=1})[ftype], "ftype must be 'part' or 'whole'")
    self.interfaces[tostring(name)] = {
        inp=input,
        ret=retrieve,
        ftype=ftype,
        ready=0
    }
end

--[[                   -
:add_recipe(machine: string, inputs: table, outputs: table[, wait: number[, bulklimit: number] ])
Add a recipe to a machine.
machine - Name of already registered machine.
inputs - List or singular entry of output items or item and count pairs. See .verify_item_list().
outputs - Same format as inputs.
wait - Time this recipe takes to craft, default 0.
bulklimit - How many of this recipe can be crafted in a batch. Most recipe would be 64.
-                   ]]--
function crafter:add_recipe(machine, inputs, outputs, wait, bulklimit)
    assert(self.interfaces[machine], "not a machine name")
    assert(type(wait) == "number", "wait time must be a number")
    local recipe = {
        machine=machine,
        inp=self.verify_item_list(inputs),
        out=self.verify_item_list(outputs),
        wait=wait
    }
    for _,p in ipairs(recipe.out) do
        if not self.gives_item[p[1]] then
            self.gives_item[p[1]] = {{#self.recipes, p[2]}}
        else
            table.insert(self.gives_item[p[1]], {#self.recipes, p[2]})
        end
    end
    
    if not bulklimit then
        if type(self.bulklimit) == "function" then
            bulklimit = self.bulklimit(recipe)
        else
            bulklimit = self.bulklimit
        end
    else
        assert(type(bulklimit) == "number", "bulklimit must be a number")
    end
    recipe.bulk = bulklimit
    table.insert(self.recipes, recipe)
end

--[[                   -
:set_bulklimit(func: function)
Set function for determining max batch size. Run before adding recipes.
-                   ]]--
function crafter:set_bulklimit(func)
    assert( -- one of
      ({[[function]]=1, number=1, [[nil]]=1})[type(func)],
    "bulklimit function required")
    self.bulklimit = func or 64
end

--[[                   -
-                   ]]--
function crafter:set_inventory(tbl)
    assert(type(tbl) == "table", "inventory table required")
    self.inventory = tbl
end

--[[                   -
-                   ]]--
function crafter:can_craft(rid)
    local rpe = self.recipes[rid]
    assert(rpe, "recipe id out of range")
    local count = math.huge
    for _,it in ipairs(rpe.inp) do
        count = math.min(count,
          math.floor(self.inventory[it[1]]/it[2])
        )
    end
    return count
end

--[[                   -
-                   ]]--
function crafter:craft_recipe(rid, count)
    local rpe = self.recipes[rid]
    assert(rpe, "recipe id out of range")
    count = math.min(count or 1, rpy.bulk, self:can_craft(rid))
    if count == 0 then
        return false
    end
    assert(count > 0, "non-positive recipe count")
    local machine = self.interfaces[rpy.machine]
    if machine.ready >= os.time() then
        return false
    end
    if machine.rid then
        self:retrieve(machine.rid)
    end
    if machine.ftype == "part" then
        for i,v in ipairs(rpy.inp) do
            machine.inp(v[1], v[2]*count, i)
        end
    elseif machine.ftype == "whole" then
        machine.inp(rpy, count)
    end
    for i,v in ipairs(rpy.inp) do
        self.inventory[v[1]] = self.inventory[v[1]] - v[2]*count
    end
    machine.ready = os.time() + rpy.wait*count
    machine.rid = rid
    machine.count = count
    return count, rpy.wait*count
end

--[[                   -
-                   ]]--
function crafter:retrieve(rid)
    if not rid then
        local n = 0
        for i=1,#self.recipes do
            if self:retrieve(i) then
                n = n + 1
            end
        end
        return n
    end
    local rpe = self.recipes[rid]
    assert(rpe, "recipe id out of range")
    local machine = self.interfaces[rpy.machine]
    if not machine.rid or machine.ready < os.time() then
        return false
    end
    if machine.ftype == "part" then
        for i,v in ipairs(rpy.out) do
            local ret = machine.ret(v[1], v[2]*count, i) or v[2]*count
            self.inventory[v[1]] = self.inventory[v[1]] + ret
        end
    elseif machine.ftype == "whole" then
        machine.ret(rpy, count)
        for k,v in pairs(rpy.inp) do
            self.inventory[v[1]] = self.inventory[v[1]] + v[2]*count
        end
    end
    machine.rid, machine.count = nil
    return true
end

--[[                   -
-                   ]]--
function crafter:craft(target, count)
    assert(self.inventory, "inventory table required")
    local slist, rlist = {{target, count}}, {}
    while #slist ~= 0 do
        item = table.remove(slist)
        if self.inventory[item[1]] >= item[2] then
            -- inventory stuff?
            goto continue
        end
        local give = self.gives_item[item[1]][1]
        local rct = math.ceil(item[2] / give[2])
        table.insert(rlist, {give[1], rct})
        for _,p in pairs(self.recipes[gives[1]].inp) do
            table.insert(slist, p)
        end
        ::continue::
    end
    for _,s in pairs(rlist) do
        self:craft_recipe(s[1], s[2])
    end
end

--[[                   -
.verify_item_list(list)
Confirm and disambiguate an item list.
Example inputs:
"stone"
{"bronze_ingot", 4}
{"tin_ingot", {"copper_ingot", 3}}
-                   ]]--
function crafter.verify_item_list(list)
    if type(list) == "string" or 
      (type(list) == "table" and type(list[2]) == "number") then
        list = {list}
    end
    assert(type(list) == "table", "item list must be a table or string")
    for i,p in ipairs(list) do
        if type(p) == "string" then
            p = {p, 1}
            list[i] = p
        end
        assert(
          type(p) == "table" or type(p[1]) == "string" or type(p[2]) == "number",
        "item list must be a table of name-count pairs or names")
    end
    return list
end

crafter.__index = crafter
setmetatable(crafter, crafter)

return crafter

yMine = 15
xMine = 15
-- mining area
-- starts from bottom left corner, mines 1, then mines bottom row, goes up, mines left, repeat

function updateOffset(walls)
  print("updating offset")
  local handle = fs.open("offset.txt", "w")
  handle.write(tostring(walls))
  handle.close()
  print("offset updated")
end
function readOffset()
  print("reading offset")
  local handle = fs.open("offset.txt", "r")
  local walls = handle.readAll()
  handle.close()
  print("offset read")
  return tonumber(walls)
end

function dropUselessItems()
  local useless = {"minecraft:cobblestone", "minecraft:dirt", "minecraft:sand", "minecraft:gravel", "minecraft:cobbled_deepslate", "minecraft:tuff"}

  for i = 1, 16 do
    local item = turtle.getItemDetail(i)
    if item and contains(useless, item.name) then
      turtle.select(i)
      turtle.drop()
    end
  end
end

function contains(table, val)
   for i=1,#table do
      if table[i] == val then 
         return true
      end
   end
   return false
end

-- starts on right side of mining area infront of chest, facing chest
coords = {x = 0, y = 0, z = 0}

function moveToLong(target)
  local directions = {
    x = target.x > coords.x and "forward" or "back",
    y = target.y > coords.y and "up" or "down",
    z = target.z > coords.z and "right" or "left"
  }

  for axis, direction in pairs(directions) do
    local difference = math.abs(target[axis] - coords[axis])

    if direction == "forward" or direction == "back" then
      if direction == "back" then
        turtle.turnRight()
        turtle.turnRight()
      end
      for i = 1, difference do
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
      end
      if direction == "back" then
        turtle.turnRight()
        turtle.turnRight()
      end
      coords.x = target.x
    elseif direction == "up" or direction == "down" then
      for i = 1, difference do
        if direction == "up" then
          turtle.digUp()
          turtle.up()
        else
          turtle.digDown()
          turtle.down()
        end
      end
      coords.y = target.y
    elseif direction == "right" or direction == "left" then
      if direction == "right" then
        turtle.turnRight()
      else
        turtle.turnLeft()
      end
      for i = 1, difference do
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
      end
      if direction == "right" then
        turtle.turnLeft()
      else
        turtle.turnRight()
      end
      coords.z = target.z
    end
  end
end

function moveToShort(target)
  if target.x == coords.x and target.y == coords.y and target.z == coords.z then
    return
  end
  local directions = {
    x = target.x > coords.x and "forward" or "back",
    y = target.y > coords.y and "up" or "down",
    z = target.z > coords.z and "right" or "left"
  }
  
  for axis, direction in pairs(directions) do
    local difference = math.abs(target[axis] - coords[axis])
    
    for i = 1, difference do
      if direction == "forward" then
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
        coords.x = coords.x + 1
      elseif direction == "back" then
        turtle.turnLeft()
        turtle.turnLeft()
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
        turtle.turnLeft()
        turtle.turnLeft()
        coords.x = coords.x - 1
      elseif direction == "up" then
        turtle.digUp()
        turtle.up()
        coords.y = coords.y + 1
      elseif direction == "down" then
        turtle.digDown()
        turtle.down()
        coords.y = coords.y - 1
      elseif direction == "right" then
        turtle.turnRight()
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
        turtle.turnLeft()
        coords.z = coords.z + 1
      elseif direction == "left" then
        turtle.turnLeft()
        turtle.dig()
        turtle.forward()
        turtle.turnRight()
        coords.z = coords.z - 1
      end
    end
  end
end

function Translate(x, y, z)
  x = x or 0
  y = y or 0
  z = z or 0
  if (math.abs(x) > 1 or math.abs(y) > 1 or math.abs(z) > 1) then
    moveToLong({x = coords.x + x, y = coords.y + y, z = coords.z + z});
  else
    moveToShort({x = coords.x + x, y = coords.y + y, z = coords.z + z});
  end
end

function dropAllToChest()
  moveToLong({x = 0, y = 0, z = 0})
  face("minecraft:chest")
for i = 1, 16 do
    if turtle.getItemCount(i) > 0 then
      turtle.select(i)
      if not turtle.drop() then
        print("Chest is full. Terminating program.")
        os.exit()
      end
    end
  end
end

-- will endless loop if no block, however this should never happen
function face(targetBlock)
  local success, data = turtle.inspect()
  if (data.name == targetBlock) or not success then
    repeat
      turtle.turnLeft()
      success, data = turtle.inspect()
    until data.name == targetBlock
  end
end

function isFull()
  dropUselessItems()
  for i = 1, 16 do
    if turtle.getItemCount(i) == 0 then
      return false
    end
  end
  return true
end

-- mine 1 block forward (X) to get into starting position
-- then mine bottom row going right
-- then mine up 1, mine left row going left
-- alternate until done all rows
-- then go back to starting position, if inventory full of unwanted items (eg full after doing dropUseless()), dump into chest,
-- then go back to starting position and repeat forever (or until chest full)
-- x++ = forward  
-- y++ = up
-- z++ = right
startingPos = {x = 1 + readOffset(), y = 0, z = 0}
skip = false
rowsMined = 0
function mine()
  while true do
    print("starting mining loop");
    -- starting from facing chest
    if (not skip) then
      print("turning around")
      turtle.turnLeft()
      turtle.turnLeft()
    end
    
    print("moving to starting position")
    moveToLong(startingPos)
    startingPos = {x = coords.x, y = coords.y, z = coords.z}

    for i = 1, yMine do
      for j = 1, xMine do
        print("mining row")
        turtle.dig();
        Translate(0,0,1);  
      end
      print("moving back to start of row")
      moveToLong(startingPos)
      print("moving up 1")
      Translate(0,1,0);
      startingPos = {x = coords.x, y = coords.y, z = coords.z}
    end
    rowsMined = rowsMined + 1
    print("Walls mined: " .. rowsMined)
    print("moving back down to bottom row and going forward")
    Translate(1, -yMine, 0)
    startingPos = {x = coords.x, y = coords.y, z = coords.z}
    print("checking if full")
    if (isFull()) then
      dropAllToChest()
      skip = false
    else 
      skip = true
    end
  end
end

In its early years, silver coins were being hoarded or exported, and the gold dollar found a ready place in commerce. Silver again circulated after Congress required in 1853 that new coins of that metal be made lighter, and the gold dollar became a rarity in commerce even before federal coins vanished from circulation amid the economic disruption of the American Civil War. Gold did not circulate again in most of the nation until 1879, and even then, the gold dollar did not regain its place in commerce. def find_smallest_lines_to_calc_kgv_for(matrix, zeile, spalte):
    """
    Returns which columns have to be multiplied by which factor shuch that the element
    at matrix[zeile][spalte] can be subtracted to 0.
    :param matrix: Matrix for Gauss
    :param zeile: Row in which target element sits
    :param spalte: Column in which target element sits
    :return: dictionary in form of {row: factor}
    """
    import numpy as np

    gesuchtes_element = matrix[zeile][spalte]
    spalten_fuer_kgv_berechnung = {}

    relevant_column = np.array(matrix)[:, spalte]

    for i in range(len(relevant_column)):
        if i == zeile or relevant_column[i] == 0:
            continue
        else:
            spalten_fuer_kgv_berechnung[i] = relevant_column[i]

    d = {}

    for element in spalten_fuer_kgv_berechnung.items():
        d[element[0]] = gesuchtes_element * element[1]

    min_key = min(d, key=lambda k: d[k])

    return {min_key: gesuchtes_element, zeile: spalten_fuer_kgv_berechnung[min_key]}


def multiply_rows_of_matrix_with_factors(matrix, factors):
    """
    Takes a certain matrix and returns the new matrix whereas every row according to the
    factors dict is multiplied with a certain factor.

    :param matrix: matrix to be transformed
    :param factors: factors in the form of d = {0: 2, 2: 3} where the key is the row and the value the factor
    :return: the transformed matrix in the form of a 2d array: [[8, 8, -4, 16], [8, 2, 4, 10], [6, 4, 1, 4]]
    """
    import numpy as np
    result_matrix = matrix
    for factor_tuple in factors.items():

        for i in range(len(result_matrix[factor_tuple[0]])):
            result_matrix[factor_tuple[0]][i] *= factor_tuple[1]

    return np.array(result_matrix)


def get_key_of_factors_being_not_searched(factors_dictionary):
    """
    Retrieves the key of a dictionary of factors that is not the searched row.
    :return:
    """
    return [e for e in list(factors_dictionary.keys()) if e != gesuchte_zeile]


gesuchte_zeile = 1
gesuchte_spalte = 0

initial_matrix = [[2, 2, -1, 4], [4, 1, 2, 5], [6, 4, 1, 4]]
print("Ausgangsmatrix ::: ")
print(initial_matrix)

print(10 * "#")

factors = find_smallest_lines_to_calc_kgv_for(initial_matrix, gesuchte_zeile, gesuchte_spalte)
print("Faktoren Dictionary ::: ")
print(factors)

print(10 * "#")

transformed_matrix = multiply_rows_of_matrix_with_factors(initial_matrix, factors)
print("Faktorisierte Matrix ::: ")
print(transformed_matrix)

print(10 * "#")

transformed_matrix[gesuchte_zeile] = (transformed_matrix[gesuchte_zeile] -
                                      transformed_matrix[get_key_of_factors_being_not_searched(factors)])
print("Neue Matrix ::: ")
print(transformed_matrix)

print(30 * "-->")

gesuchte_zeile = 2
gesuchte_spalte = 0

factors = find_smallest_lines_to_calc_kgv_for(transformed_matrix, 2, 0)
print("Faktoren Dictionary ::: ")
print(factors)

print(10 * "#")

transformed_matrix = multiply_rows_of_matrix_with_factors(transformed_matrix, factors)
print("Faktorisierte Matrix ::: ")
print(transformed_matrix)

print(10 * "#")


transformed_matrix[gesuchte_zeile] = transformed_matrix[gesuchte_zeile] - transformed_matrix[
    get_key_of_factors_being_not_searched(factors)]

print(transformed_matrix)

print(30 * "-->")
